Title: CRISPR-Cas9 Gene Editing: Ethical Considerations and Regulatory Frameworks
Authors: Dr. Jennifer Adams, Dr. Kenji Yamamoto
Published: Bioethics Journal, Volume 38, Issue 2, 2024
DOI: 10.1111/bioe.13142

Abstract:
This paper examines the evolving ethical landscape surrounding CRISPR-Cas9 
gene editing technology, with particular focus on germline editing, somatic
cell therapy, and agricultural applications. We compare regulatory frameworks
across 20 countries and propose harmonized guidelines.

Keywords: CRISPR, gene editing, bioethics, regulation, germline editing
